“Growing up in a family with a proud Peruvian father and beautiful bohemian mother, has meant I have grown up in an environment a little different from most. Exotic objects filled our home, such as giant green snail shells, huge seed pods and ancient pots lining the shelves. There were swirls of bright colours in our Andean textiles covering the walls and furniture and of course the sound of my father playing his pan-pipes drifted through the halls. I have been engulfed in a world of curiosities.
